  "text": "Microplots. Twenty microplots were established in April 2000 on a sand-based putting green at the Rocky Ford Turfgrass Research Center, Manhattan, KS. The green, which was seeded to A-4 creeping bentgrass at 49 kg/ha in fall 1998, had a root zone of 97.5% sand and 2.5% clay and a pH of 7.5. Microplots were spaced 1 m apart in a 4-by-5-m area. Each microplot consisted of a 30.5-cm-diameter schedule 40 polyvinylchloride (PVC) tube (Diamond Plastics Corp, Grand Island, NE) placed into the green to a depth of 38 cm. The construction of these microplots was previously described by Settle et al. [CITATION_1] .",
